The paper deals with problems related to computational geometry, specifically the Erdős-Szekeres theorem and testing weak epsilon nets. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves complexity theory and NP-hardness, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The use of combinatorial arguments and the study of sets and subsets suggest cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the mention of graphs and networks in the paper suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
